# {{entomology|botany}} A [[chamber]] produced by a [[plant]] in which [[insect]]s, [[mite]]s, or [[fungus|fungi]] live. It typically takes the form of a [[hollow]] in a [[leaf]], or a system of tunnels in a [[thorn]] or [[stem]]. A domatium is generally a [[mutualistic]] [[adaptation]], not to be confused with simple damage by a [[borer]] or [[gall]]-forming [[pest]].

